p: The mean methb% was 23.8% (±11.5 [SD]) and median CYB5R activity was 10.9% (Q1, Q3;5.8,24.1). Dogs homozygous for the Arg219Pro variant had significantly greater methb% (36.2± 9.9%) and more clinical signs than those homozygous for Ile190Leu variant (15.7%, 6.0, P < 0.001). Beside cyanosis, 70% of dogs exhibited ≥1 other clinical sign.
